@*Movie - Iron Lung | Genre - Horror | Thoughts - Iron Lung is a horror film that relies heavily on atmosphere and tension to create its unsettling effect. The movie's pacing is deliberate, allowing the audience to build up dread before the inevitable scares. 
It also does not heavily rely on jump scares like many other horror titles. While it may lack the polish of bigger-budget films, it succeeds in creating a genuinely creepy experience. | 
Real Facts - Iron Lung makes use of 80000 gallons of fake blood, the most used in any horror title to date. *@
@*Movie - GOAT | Genre - Sports | Thoughts - While similar to Zootopia in setting, GOAT starts off in what could be called the slums of Zootopia and follows Will Harris, a young (anthropomorphic) goat who dreams of joining his favorite roarball team, the Thorns. 
He finally gets his chance when his initial trouncing of a top player goes viral and gains the attention of the team's owner. GOAT's story could be considered formulaic and predictable, but the story is done so well and with such passion that it hardly matters.
Real facts - Lenny Williamson, a giraffe, is voiced by Stephen Curry, a famously short basketball player *@